          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-03 15:44:15.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: introduce LNET_PEER_MULTI_RAIL flag bit",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: introduce LNET_PEER_MULTI_RAIL flag bit\n\nAdd lp_state as a flag word to lnet_peer, and add lp_lock\nto protect it. This lock needs to be taken whenever the\nfield is updated, because setting or clearing a bit is\na read-modify-write cycle.\n\nThe lp_multi_rail is removed, its function is replaced by\nthe new LNET_PEER_MULTI_RAIL flag bit.\n\nThe helper lnet_peer_is_multi_rail() tests the bit.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: I7e5678d75b2563d26896d3e108ce8ece0487dc48\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
